subSubSection.paragraph:
Prosoma.
Carapace reddish-brown, with a wide median longitudinal band and three triangular spots of white and black setae (
Fig. 1
); marginal stripes yellow, wide and continuous with distinct reddish-brown spots; black around all eyes (
Figs 3–4
). Sternum uniformly black, covered with black setae. Chelicerae dark brown, proximally covered with long white setae, distally with black setae. Endites dark brown, pale apically. Clypeus yellow, covered with black setae. Labium dark brown, covered with black setae (
Figs 2–3
).
